President Cyril Rmaphosa addresses crowds at his inauguration at Loftus Stadium on Saturday morning. JOHANNESBURG - Thousands of South Africans attended President Cyril Ramaphosa's inauguration on Saturday at Loftus Versfeld Stadium. WATCH: President Cyril Ramaphosa's inauguration The president's swearing-in ceremony was bigger and cheaper than previous such events, as it moved from the Union Buildings to the rugby stadium. Guests who attended the event include DA leader Mmusi Maimane, EFF leader Julius Malema, former public protector Thuli Madonsela, Mandla Mandela and Cosatu president Zigiswa Losi. The Loftus Versfeld Stadium was filled with excitement as thousands of South African citizens witnessed and celebrated President Cyril Ramaphosa's inauguration.  Mandla Mandela and his wife Rabia Clarke attend the presidents inauguration at the Loftus Versfeld Stadium on Saturday. EFF leader Julius Malema and the party's General secretary Godrich Gardee. The Loftus Versfeld Stadium was filled with excitement as thousands of South African citizens witnessed and celebrated President Cyril Ramaphosa's inauguration. Former President FW de Klerk and his wife arrive for the Presidential Inauguration. Deputy President David Mabuza has and his wife arrive waves to the crowds as he arrives for the presidential inauguration. UDM leader Bantu Holomisa and Penny Penny pose for a picture at Loftus Versfeld on Saturday during the presidential inauguration. More than 30,000 people including world leaders descended on Loftus Stadium on Saturday morning for President Cyril Ramaphosa's inauguration.